definitions.definition: Belonging to the sex which typically produces sperm , or to the gender which is typically associated with it.
Characteristic of this sex / gender . ( Compare masculine , manly . )
Tending to lead to or regulate the development of sexual characteristics typical of this sex .
Masculine ; of the masculine grammatical gender.
Having the F factor ; able to impart DNA into another bacterium which does not have the F factor (a female ).
Of instruments, tools, or connectors: designed to fit into or penetrate a female counterpart, as in a connector , pipe fitting or laboratory glassware .

main_definition: Belonging to the sex which typically produces sperm , or to the gender which is typically associated with it. [from 14th c.]
secondary_definitions: Characteristic of this sex / gender . ( Compare masculine , manly . )
Tending to lead to or regulate the development of sexual characteristics typical of this sex .

( of bacteria ) Having the F factor ; able to impart DNA into another bacterium which does not have the F factor (a female ).
